<task id="R7-095" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Wire Library modal into briefing widget (FR-18)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>9</wave>
    <estimated-effort>2-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>code-page, ui, wave-9</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>094</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-18 (consumer surface 2 of 3)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wire the Playbook Library modal into the Daily Briefing widget
    (src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/). Add a "Browse Playbooks" affordance at
    the mount point recommended by task 093's audit. When clicked, the affordance opens the
    PlaybookLibraryShell modal. The modal lists every playbook with its consumer mapping. Clicking
    a playbook invokes it through proper Path A.5 routing. Reuse the shared PlaybookLibraryShell
    component AND mirror the pattern established by task 094 in the spaarke-ai chat surface.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React / Fluent UI v9 developer familiar with Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components and the
    "shared lib widget + thin host shim" pattern (Calendar canonical Pattern D per SPAARKEAI-COMPONENTIZATION-AUDIT.md).
  </role>

  <goal>
    Daily Briefing widget now has a "Browse Playbooks" affordance such that:
    1. Affordance mounted at the location task 093 audit recommended for the briefing widget
       (e.g., DailyBriefingApp toolbar, header action menu, or per-section overflow).
    2. Affordance triggers a modal Dialog wrapping PlaybookLibraryShell (the shared component from
       Spaarke.UI.Components). Same modal wrapper pattern as task 094.
    3. Modal lists every playbook with its consumer mapping (consumer code visible per row).
    4. Clicking a playbook invokes it through Path A.5 routing — verified by inspecting BFF log
       or behavioral check. Briefing widget context (current date range, channel filter, etc.)
       MAY be passed to invocation if the selected playbook is briefing-aware; otherwise default
       payload.
    5. Affordance follows ADR-021 (dark mode semantic tokens; no hardcoded colors).
    6. Component test added at src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/test/PlaybookLibraryAffordance.test.tsx
       (or equivalent — mirror existing test pattern in same dir) confirming affordance opens
       modal + selection callback fires.
    7. No new app-level state library; use existing pattern.
    8. Pattern parity with task 094 — review both for consistency before commit.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="audit-doc">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/playbook-library-audit.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="shared-modal-component">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/PlaybookLibraryShell/PlaybookLibraryShell.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="briefing-widget">src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/src/components/DailyBriefingApp.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="briefing-test-pattern">src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/test/DailyBriefingApp.smoke.test.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="task-094-pattern">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/{wired-in-094}.tsx</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — playbook launch from modal MUST flow through IInvokePlaybookAi triangle (Path A.5). NO direct PlaybookOrchestrationService call.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021 (referenced)">Dark mode compliance — affordance + modal use semantic Fluent UI tokens, no hardcoded colors.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-18">Acceptance: "Browse Playbooks" affordance opens modal; modal lists every playbook + consumer mapping; clicking invokes through Path A.5 routing.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Component justification triple:
      1. Existing: PlaybookLibraryShell shared component already exists. Task 094 just wired the same modal into spaarke-ai chat. Reuse the same Dialog wrapper pattern.
      2. Extension: this task adds the affordance + Dialog wrapper in the briefing widget. NO new shared component; NO duplication of task 094's wiring pattern (mirror it).
      3. Cost-of-doing-nothing: briefing widget users cannot in-flow browse + invoke any playbook from the briefing surface; FR-18 acceptance criterion (≥3 consumer surfaces wired) not met.
    </constraint>
    <constraint source="fluent-v9-component skill">Apply Fluent UI v9 patterns + Spaarke conventions.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>code-pages/daily-briefing</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-013-bff-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-COMPONENTIZATION-AUDIT.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-COMPONENT-MODEL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/fluent-v9-component/SKILL.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="PlaybookLibraryShell shared component" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/PlaybookLibraryShell/PlaybookLibraryShell.tsx">
        Reuse via Dialog wrapper.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Task 094 wiring pattern" location="src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/{wired-in-094}.tsx">
        Mirror this affordance + Dialog wrapper structure for consistency.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Daily Briefing widget is consumer surface 2 of 3 for FR-18. Task 094 wired the same modal into
      spaarke-ai chat (surface 1). Task 096 will wire surface 3 (ad-hoc launcher). Pattern parity
      between 094/095/096 matters: 3 separate hosts, ONE Dialog wrapper recipe, ONE PlaybookLibraryShell reuse.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="093" status="required">Audit doc with mount-point recommendation for the briefing widget.</dependency>
      <dependency task="094" status="required">Establishes the Dialog wrapper + Path A.5 invocation pattern this task mirrors.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Briefing widget today: DailyBriefingApp.tsx. Pattern D dual-use (Calendar widget canonical).</item>
      <item>Task 094 wiring — mirror its structure for consistency.</item>
      <item>Task 096 — ad-hoc launcher next.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: code-impl in Code Page (.tsx file modification, tags code-page + ui, ADR-013+021 applicable, FR-18 acceptance criterion) — quality gates Step 9.5 required · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md (FR-18) + plan.md (Wave 9) + task 093 audit doc + task 094 wiring (for pattern parity).
      Invoke the fluent-v9-component skill.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Verify dependency">
      Confirm task 094 is complete + committed. Confirm audit doc's recommended briefing-widget mount point is unambiguous.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Read DailyBriefingApp host component">
      Open src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/src/components/DailyBriefingApp.tsx
      (+ any sibling toolbar/header components). Identify the recommended mount point's exact insertion site.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Read task 094's wiring as pattern template">
      Open the file modified in task 094 (likely under src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/).
      Document the Dialog wrapper structure, state management, props passed to PlaybookLibraryShell,
      and the Path A.5 invocation callback. This task mirrors that pattern.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Wire affordance at recommended mount point">
      Add a "Browse Playbooks" Button at the recommended mount point in DailyBriefingApp.tsx (or
      sibling). Wire onClick to open Dialog state (useState in the host component).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Wrap PlaybookLibraryShell in Dialog">
      Mirror task 094's Dialog wrapper. Same DialogSurface / DialogBody / DialogContent / DialogActions
      structure. PlaybookLibraryShell as DialogContent body. Pass the same props pattern.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Wire playbook-selected callback to Path A.5">
      Mirror task 094's invocation pattern. If briefing-widget context (date range, channel filter)
      should be passed when invoking briefing-aware playbooks, pass it via the invocation payload;
      otherwise default payload. MUST flow through IInvokePlaybookAi (Path A.5).
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="ADR-021 dark mode compliance">
      Verify affordance + Dialog use semantic tokens. Dark mode toggle smoke.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Component test">
      Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/test/PlaybookLibraryAffordance.test.tsx
      (or alongside existing DailyBriefingApp.smoke.test.tsx). Test:
      - Affordance renders
      - Click opens Dialog (mock PlaybookLibraryShell as stub)
      - onPlaybookSelected callback fires
      - Dialog closes
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Build + test">
      Run: npm run build:prod for Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components (or the consuming app — check existing build script).
      Run: npm test for the new test.
      Goal: 0 errors; new test passes.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Manual smoke">
      Deploy to spaarkedev1 dev or document for owner to deploy. Manual smoke: open briefing widget
      → click "Browse Playbooks" → modal opens → modal lists playbooks WITH consumer mapping →
      click a playbook → invocation flows through Path A.5 (verify by checking BFF logs).
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `/code-review` on new affordance + test. Run `/adr-check` against ADR-013 + ADR-021 + spec FR-18.
      Verify pattern parity with task 094 (cite the mirror in PR description).
      Fix any findings before commit.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 095 status complete; advance current-task.md to task 096.
    </step>
    <step order="13" name="Commit">
      Commit affordance + Dialog wrapper + test with conventional message.
      Example: feat(daily-briefing/r7): wire Playbook Library modal into briefing widget (Wave 9 task 095, FR-18)
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read (audit doc, shared component, briefing widget files, task 094 wiring for mirror)</tool>
    <tool>Edit (add affordance + Dialog wrapper)</tool>
    <tool>Write (component test file)</tool>
